quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  72,1,"Say<a class=",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is <i>jinn</i> which are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.,footnotes:2:The Arabic word used is <i>Qur’an</i> which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  72,2,"that guides to prudence, so we have come to believe in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord."
  72,3,"<span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Ibn ‘Amer, Abu Ja’far, Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “And indeed…”</span>
  72,4,"And thatd our fool used to speak untruthfully about Allah."
  72,5,"<span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Ibn ‘Amer, Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “And indeed…”</span>,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…would never attribute a lie to Allah.”</span>
  72,6,"And thatd certain men among humans used to seek refuge in certain men among the unseen beings, but they only increased them in confusion."
  72,7,"And thata they thought, as youpl thought, that Allah would never resurrect anyone."
  72,8,"And thata we sought to reach the heaven and found it filled with stern guards and meteors."
  72,9,"And thata we used to take up positions to listen in, but whoever listens now finds a meteor in wait for him."
  72,10,"And thata we do not know whether ill has been desired for those on earth, or if their Lord has desired prudence for them."